data.title: New Owners, Great Food
data.text: I think I found my new favourite place in Wormtown.  I've been working in downtown Worcester for the last few weeks so I looked for a place to eat lunch close by.  We found the Midtown Dinette tucked inside the Midtown mall by City Hall off Main and Front streets.  They serve breakfast all day (6-3) but it is their lunch specials I really like.  Fridays fish 'n chips was Great, not to mention the extra large piece if fish.  Monday they had stuffed peppers, honest, 2 even, almost too much to eat.  Today, election day, I had the homemade chicken soup and chicken parm over pasta.  I tell you, i'm gonna gain 20 lbs if I keep eating here.  Might have to try the salads for the rest of the week, they look good.

data.title: Ditch the paper plates.
data.text: Sorry,but I was a regular for a few weeks until they switched to serving the food on paper plates. Nothing worse than over easy eggs and greezy homefries served on paper ! Colorful crowd though,interesting, but not well thought out overly lighted diner decor. Waitresses on duty constantly using their cellphones does not cut the mustard. Loose the paper plates !!!

data.title: I really like this place. Food is good, service is very friendly and fast, and it's very inexpensive.
